form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Information about your residences and employment., Form N-4 (00 ( (Rev 07/17'91)N

full_text: Screened by NARA, 6/29/2023 Part 4. Information about your residences and employment. 1. List your addresses during the last five (5) years or since you became a permanent resident, whichever IS less. Begin with your current address. If you need more space, continue on separate paper: Dates (month/day/year) Street Number and Name, City, State, Country, and Zip Code From To 3549 S. "B" STREET OXNARD, CALIFORNIA 93033 01-01-97 PRESENT 612 JOYCE DRIVE PORT HUENEME, CALIFORNIA 93041 01-01-91 01-01-97 B. List your employers during the last five (5) years. List your present or most recent employer first. If none, write "None". If you need more space, continue on separate paper. Employer's Name Employer's Address Dates Employed (month/day/year) Occupation/position Street Name and Number - City, State and ZIP Code From To RETIRED SINCE NONE 05-1968 Part 5. Information about your marital history. A. Total number of times you have been married 1 If you are now married, complete the following regarding your husband or wife. Family name Given name Middle initial MARTINEZ-ALCANTAR ROSA Address 3549 S. "B" STREET OXNARD, CALIFORNIA 93033 Date of birth Country of birth Citizenship (month/day/year) 09-06-1912 MEXICO MEXICAN Social A# (if applicable) Immigration status Security# 552-88-1513 A17222774 (If not a U.S. citizen) LEGAL RESIDENT Naturalization (If applicable) (month/day/year) N/A Place (City, State) N/A If you have ever previously been married or if your current spouse has been previously married, please provide the following on separate paper: Name of prior spouse, date of marriage, date marriage ended, how marriage ended and immigration status of prior spouse. Part 6. Information about your children. B. Total Number of Children 2 Complete the following information for each of your children. II the child lives with you, state "with me" in the address column; otherwise give city/state/country of child's current residence. If deceased, write "deceased" in the address column. If you need more space, continue on separate paper.
